      "alt": "23:11:14  slagworks-power→slagworks-prime\n    PR #22 review/roast loop: addressed B3-symmetry on identity-check matcher, MAC builder %02x bug, leftover 'want ready' in TestReCommission. CI re-running. Will\n    merge\n    once green. Then starting PLA-491 group 1 (refactor C, 7 cells, missing-efivarfs as highest-value). For PR #19 review findings: filing as a single consolidated\n    cleanup issue per your guidance — will do that next, before #22 finishes CI.\n\n23:15:34  slagworks-sshd→slagworks-prime\n    review fixes pushed to PR #20 (commit 89a8d41).\n\n    addressed all 5 of the \"ADDRESS NOW\" items:\n\n    1. bootSSHKeys: pure-fn test for stripSSHKeyComment + testpg integration test (200/204/no-auth). pre-commit roast caught a real bug — naive parts[0]+parts[1]\n    discards key material when the line starts with options ('restrict ssh-ed25519 ...' or 'command=\"...\" ...'). fixed to sniff parts[0] for a known key-type prefix\n    and keep parts[0..2] otherwise. covered with test cases.\n    2. end-of-build warning when deploy + CI-unset + no fetch: emitted right after the \"Built: $TARBALL\" line so it can't be buried.\n    3. fixed the wrong comment in build.sh — recovery_drop DOES get reached on commission agent-failure; the no-keys branch is exactly what makes that path safe.\n    4. comment scrubbing on /boot/ssh-keys emit (the security one — keys public, comments aren't an operator roster handed to recon).\n    5. set +e at top of recovery_drop; body now safe through mkdir/chmod/heredoc.\n\n    bonus: cpio-concat invariant comment in the qemu test for the next reader.\n\n    deferred per your \"CONSIDER\" tag → filed:\n\n    • PLA-512: slagctl deploy --recovery --watch hangs for full op timeout\n    • PLA-513: gate SLAGWORKS_FATAL_AT to test-only build tag\n\n    both filed in PLA team. lnx 0.2.0-dev doesn't have a --project flag so I tagged scope via comments. (could be worth a PR to lnx itself; out of slagworks scope.)\n\n    CI rebuilding. ping when something interesting happens.\n\n23:…",
